<HEADLINE>
PREP THROWS FOR 724 YARDS
</HEADLINE>
 (NOTE TO EDITORS: Van Nuys and Pacific Palisades are both
neighborhoods of the city of Los Angeles) 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JULIO CORTEZ  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ David Koral of Pacific Palisades passed for 724
yards against Grant of Van Nuys Friday afternoon, shattering the
state single-game high school record by 160 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Koral, a senior, also threw seven touchdown passes. He completed
34 of 53 attempts _ averaging 21.3 yards a completion in slippery
and sometimes rainy conditions as Palisades (2-1) defeated host
Grant 48-30.
</P>
<P>
   The previous state record was set in 1996 by Doug Baughman of
Bolsa Grande High of Garden Grove in a 53-23 victory over La Quinta
High of Westminster.
</P>
<P>
   His first-half touchdowns went to Charles Ealy (80 and 15 yards)
and Greig Carlson (42 and 52 yards).
</P>
<P>
   Carlson, who caught nine passes for 249 yards, added his third
touchdown on a third-down, 94-yard strike from Koral.
</P>
<P>
   Eric Beegun finished with five catches for 133 yards, including
touchdowns of 90 and 36 yards. Ealy caught 13 balls for 226 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Perry Clayton, who intercepted Koral in the first quarter, led
Grant (1-2) with 276 rushing yards and three touchdowns _ all in
the third quarter _ on runs of 40 and 46 yards.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
