relationship with Lewinsky.
</P>
<P>
   Athletic Oddities in Sydney
</P>
<P>
   The Olympics began to look a little like a soap opera, which
could only boost NBC's anemic ratings.
</P>
<P>
   First, the French runn Marie-Jose Perec, the defending champion
in the women's 200 and 400 meters, said she would not compete and
flew to Singapore. Perec claimed to have been threatened by a man
who forced his way into her Sydney hotel room, but Australian
