<P>
   Coxnet LIFESTYLES 0923: FALL GARDENING -- Fall, the best
gardening season of all, is officially here _ so get organized.
True, spring holds lots of promise for gardeners, avid and amateur
alike. But autumn gives many plants their best shot at success
because they'll have all winter to rest up before they're forced to
battle the summer stresses of heat, drought, insects and disease.
(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). Art includes a 4-column
color photo of a fall garden next to a house.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: GARDENING CHART _ A chart showing gardening tasks that
need to be preformed in September and October. Art includes seven
1-column color photos.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: FURNACE UPDATE _ To those conscientious folks who are
never late with an oil change, who have a complete physical every
year and who keep track of everybody's birthday, this is a gentle
reminder: It's time to think about scheduling your annual furnace
inspection and cleaning. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL 0919: RETURN TO MAYBERRY -- Mount Airy, N.C., has
become a quiet mecca for cultists of black-and-white TV reruns and
archaeologists of 1960s innocence. Each year, thousands make the
pilgrimage to this tidy town in the Blue Ridge Mountains to
preserve the memory of the town's most celebrated citizen: Andy
Griffith. You see, Mount Airy is renowned for its alter-ego _ that
as Mayberry, the mythical setting for ``The Andy Griffith Show.''
(Moffett, Palm Beach Post) Art includes a 3-column color photo of
downtown Mount Airy, a 2-column color photo of a barbershop and a
18-pica color photo of an old-fashioned police car.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: Trivia questions from ``The Andy Griffith Show.''
</P>
<P>
   WITH: FLORIDIAN IN DULUTH: Minnesotans don't realize that most
of us in Florida think they're crazy for living there. So I risk
severe condemnation for releasing the following secret: Duluth is a
beautiful city, among the best places in the United States to spend
the early fall. (Bierman, Palm Beach Post) Art includes a 18-pica
color photo of a waterfalls near Duluth, Minn.
</P>
