<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, SEPT. 23 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-VATICAN-POLITICS-NYT (moved Tuesday, Sepember 19) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Sepember
19 about reassignments at the Vatican misspelled the given name of
one co-author of an article in the Jesuit magazine America that
suggested that the Vatican was growing more tolerant about the use
of condoms to combat the spread of AIDS, and misspelled the surname
of the other. The authors are the Rev. Jon D. Fuller (not John) and
the Rev. James F. Keenan (not Keegan).
</P>
<P>
   BC-BUSH-ADVISER-NYT (moved Wednesday, September 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday,
September 20 about a health care policy adviser to Gov. George W.
Bush who has financial ties to eight health care companies referred
incorrectly to her ownership of 16,000 options on shares in United
Health Care, of which she is a director. The adviser, Dr. Gail R.
Wilensky, sold the shares in May at a profit of $328,144; she does
not still hold them.
</P>
<P>
   The article also misstated the name of one company in which Dr.
Wilensky holds an interest. It is St. Jude Medical Inc., not St.
Jude Medical Care.
</P>
<P>
   FLA-POLS-ETIQUETTE (moved Sunday, September 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, September
10 about rules of decorum established by the City Commission of
Coral Gables, Fla., for its meetings included an erroneous account
from a resident about a warning given her by Mayor Raul
Valdes-Fauli. The mayor warned that the resident, Roxcy Bolton, who
spoke passionately at a meeting, would be removed if she offended
commission members or cast aspersions on their honesty. He did not
say he would have her arrested.
</P>
</TEXT>
