<SLUG> BC-CAMPAIGN-LEAK-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STIR OVER DEBATE INQUIRY 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Aides to Gov. George W. Bush responded sharply Saturday to an
Associated Press report that law enforcement officials were
investigating whether someone in Bush's camp had leaked materials
about his debate preparations to an associate of Vice President Al
Gore.
</P>
<P>
   Karen P. Hughes, Bush's communications director, said that
Bush's campaign manager, Joseph Allbaugh, was calling the Federal
Bureau of Investigation to complain. ``If they have identified a
suspect, Governor Bush would like to know,'' Hughes said. ``It is
completely inappropriate and wrong for the Justice Department to
play politics by leaking information in the midst of a presidential
campaign.''
</P>
<P>
   A federal law enforcement official told The Associated Press on
Friday that someone had been tentatively identified as a source of
the debate materials.
</P>
<P>
   The official would not say who it was, but said that early
evidence pointed to someone in the Bush camp.
</P>
<P>
   The FBI was called in when a Gore adviser, Tom Downey, a former
member of Congress, alerted law enforcement officials on Sept. 13
that he had been sent the package of materials.
</P>
<P>
   Downey, who had been helping Gore in debate preparations,
recused himself from further debate-preparation sessions with Gore.
</P>
</TEXT>
