   9. JUDGMENT IN DEATH, by J.D. Robb. (Berkley, $7.50.)
</P>
<P>
   Lt. Eve Dallas' investigation of the bludgeoning death
</P>
<P>
   of a police officer in a strip joint uncovers a private
</P>
<P>
   club called Purgatory.
</P>
<P>
   10. THE ALIBI, by Sandra Brown. (Warner, $7.99.)
</P>
<P>
   Jealousy, intrigue and corruption beset a Charleston
</P>
<P>
   lawyer during his pursuit of public office.
</P>
<P>
   11. LEFT BEHIND, by Tim LaHaye and Jerry B. Jenkins.
</P>
<P>
   (Tyndale, $13.99 and $7.99.) Life as lived by those
</P>
<P>
   who survive a global cataclysm. (b)
</P>
