   13. PLAINSONG, by Kent Haruf. (Vintage Contemporaries,
</P>
<P>
   $13.) A half-dozen members of a high-plains Colorado
</P>
<P>
   community learn to contend with the variety of problems
</P>
<P>
   that face them.
</P>
<P>
   14. AFTER DARK, by Jayne Ann Krentz writing as Jayne
</P>
<P>
   Castle. (Jove, $6.99.) A woman discovers a dead body
</P>
<P>
   in a low-rent museum of ancient horrors.
</P>
